com.gh.bmd.rfc.android.iterator

Interface LongSparseArrayIterable<V>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the element value type.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Iterable<LongSparseArrayEntry<V>>, SparseIterable<LongSparseArrayEntry<V>>

    public interface LongSparseArrayIterable<V>
extends SparseIterable<LongSparseArrayEntry<V>>
    This interface extends the SparseIterable one by adding specific methods handling LongSparseArrayEntry elements.

    Created by davide on 3/10/14.

      • fillImmutable

        <T> LongSparseArrayIterable<V> fillImmutable(T[] array)
        Fills the specified array with an immutable copy of the elements returned by this iterable, in the iteration order.

        Note that, if the immutable copy of the elements returned by the iterable cannot be cast to the array elements type, a ClassCastException will be thrown.

        Note also that, in case the array is not big enough to contain all the elements, an IndexOutOfBoundsException will be thrown.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the array element type.
        Parameters:
        array - the array to fill.
        Returns:
        this iterable.

      • fillImmutable

                                           int offset)
        Fills the specified array with an immutable copy of the elements returned by this iterable, in the iteration order, starting from the specified offset inside the array.

        Note that, if the immutable copy of the elements returned by the iterable cannot be cast to the array elements type, a ClassCastException will be thrown.

        Note also that, in case the array is not big enough to contain all the elements, an IndexOutOfBoundsException will be thrown.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the array element type.
        Parameters:
        array - the array to fill.
        offset - the offset from which to start filling the array.
        Returns:
        this iterable.

      • translate

        <T> LongSparseArrayIterable<T> translate(LongTranslator keyTranslator,
                                       Translator<V,T> valueTranslator)
        Returns a new iterable whose elements are the same as this ones but translated through the specified translators.

        Note that, in case the passed translator is not bidirectional, every attempt to modify the returned iterable elements will cause an exception to be thrown. Note also that all the filters and the iteration order are retained in the translation.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the new iterable element value type.
        Parameters:
        keyTranslator - the translator used to convert the element key.
        valueTranslator - the translator used to convert the element value.
        Returns:
        the new iterable.

        Parameters:
